--======================================--
--             Requisites               --
--======================================--

gcc - installed and in path
sdcc - installed and in path
sparc-elf-gcc - installed and in path
tsim_eval or tsim - installed and in path
isasim - built, installed and in path
isasim_debug - built, installed and in path

--======================================--
--             Installation             --
--======================================--

1) Place makefile mipsc.pl mipsc.sh in a folder in a specific path.

2) Alternatives 2.a or 2.b:
2.a) Create a symbolic link to mipsc.sh and place it in a directory stored in the Environmental Path Variable.
	- cd /path/to/mipscInstallPath/
	- ln -s /usr/local/bin/mipsc mipsc.sh
	- ln -s /usr/local/bin/mipsc_auto mipsc_auto.sh
2.b) Add /path/to/mipscInstallPath/ path to Environmental Path Variable. (TO BE CHECKED AND VERIFIED)
	- open file ~/bashrc, and add following lines:
		if [ -d /path/to/mipscInstallPath/ ]; then
		    $PATH = $PATH:/path/to/mipscInstallPath/
		fi
	- execute command in terminal:
		# touch ~/bashrc

--======================================--
--                Scripts               --
--======================================--

makefile file provides:
	commands to build,
	commands to use gcov and isasim functionalities.
	commands to manage produced files by place them in the correct path.

mipsc.pl:
	parse gcov and isasim oputputs
	compute TPI avarage, CCPI avarage and variance
	report for each input incite: number of executed instruction, execution time, TPI, CCPI
	report CCPI min, max, avarage, variance, standard deviation.

mipsc.sh:
	perform the process for mipsc calculation.
	It calls with the proper order the makefile and perl functionalities.

input_gen.sh:
	automatically generates input incites.

--======================================--
--             How to use               --
--======================================--
Manage inputs
	To add an input, just add a folder into includes:
		The folder name will be selected as identifier for the incite.
		The folder shall contain a file named values.h which contains the values for input variable.
	Alternatively use the mipsc_auto command, to generate automatically the inputs

Change program name
	To change the name of the test, just modify the name of the c program file

